 ICC writes to BCCI, PCB
A STAFF REPORTERCalcutta: The ICC chief executive officer Malcolm Speed Saturday confirmed he has written to both the BCCI and PCB asking for their comments on reports of racism during matches this week. We have noted media reports of racist chanting during the IndiaAustralia ODI in Vadodara on Thursday and also of racist abuse directed at South Africa players and team officials in Lahore, said Speed in an ICC release on Saturday. In the light of those reports we have written to both the BCCI and the PCB asking for their comments on the incidents. Reiterating the ICCs zero-tolerance to racism, Speed said: The Anti-Racism Code, which was strengthened last year, outlines measures host members are expected to undertake and those measures were unanimously approved by the ICCs board. With the ICC board set to meet in Dubai at the end of this month there is scope for discussion on this subjec, he added. 
